  var _root;

  if (!root) {
    return UnifiedTracking;
  }

  root.UnifiedTracking = UnifiedTracking;

  UnifiedTracking.sendAnalytic = function sendAnalytic(eventName, dataBlob) {
    root.dataLayer = root.dataLayer || [];

    if (Array.isArray(root.dataLayer)) {
      // Don't use a spread operator here for babel reasons
      dataBlob.event = dataBlob.event || eventName;
      root.dataLayer.push(dataBlob);
    }

      success: true
    });
  };

                         <span>
                          Biden, in National Address, Directs States to Move Up Vaccine Eligibility
                         </span>
                        </h3>
                       </a>
                       <div class="css-1a00rns e16ry1jj0" color="orange">
                       </div>
                       <a class="css-kej3w4" data-story="nyt://promo/283c5142-19df-5629-8bd4-157d3f59e783" data-uri="nyt://promo/283c5142-19df-5629-8bd4-157d3f59e783" data-visited="" href="https://www.nytimes.com/live/2021/03/11/us/joe-biden-news/">
                        <ul class="css-ipcj49">
                         <li>
                          President Biden called for states to make all adults eligible for a vaccine by May 1 just hours after signing a $1.9 trillion relief bill.
                         </li>
                         <li>
                          Life in the United States could return to a kind of normal by the Fourth of July, he said, but he urged continued vigilance.
                         </li>
                         <li>
                          The speech offered a renewed sense of optimism one year after the World Health Organization declared a pandemic. Heres the latest.
                         </li>

    var supports_import = false;
    var can_use_import = location.hostname.indexOf('preview.n' + 'yt.net') == -1;
    var shimport_url = window.NYTG.VIRUS_ASSETS + "/shimport@1.0.1.js";
    var shimport_promise;

    try {
      new Function("if(0)import('')")();
      supports_import = true;
    } catch(e) { }

    if (!can_use_import || !supports_import) {
      shimport_promise = new Promise(function(fulfil, reject) {
        var s = document.createElement("script");
        s.src = shimport_url;
        s.onload = function() {
          fulfil(__shimport__);
        };
        s.onerror = reject;

        document.head.appendChild(s);
      });
    }

    window.NYTG.load = function(module) {
      var url = new URL(module, location.href).href;

      if (can_use_import && supports_import) {
        return eval("import('" + url + "')");
      } else {
        return shimport_promise.then(function(shimport) {
          return shimport.load(url);
        });
      }
    };

    // for --live
    window.NYTG.subscribers = {};
    window.NYTG.watch = function(url, cb) {
      if (!window.NYTG.subscribers[url]) window.NYTG.subscribers[url] = [];
      window.NYTG.subscribers[url].push(cb);
      window.NYTG.load(url).then(cb);
    };

    var cache = new Map();
    window.NYTG.fetch = url => {
      if (!cache.has(url)) {
        cache.set(url, fetch(url).then(r => r.json().catch(err => {
          cache.delete(url);
          throw err;
        })));
      }
      return cache.get(url);
    }
  }());

                      <script>
                       Promise.all([
							NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/e967b470d8b9a8d8d0b07e76e9bf5a0252f07531/data/timeseries/en/USA-only.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/e967b470d8b9a8d8d0b07e76e9bf5a0252f07531/data/timeseries/en/NYT-World-only.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/e967b470d8b9a8d8d0b07e76e9bf5a0252f07531/data/timeseries/en/CAN.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/e967b470d8b9a8d8d0b07e76e9bf5a0252f07531/data/us_counties.json"), NYTG.fetch("https://static01.nyt.com/newsgraphics/2020/03/16/coronavirus-maps/e967b470d8b9a8d8d0b07e76e9bf5a0252f07531/data/vaccine_summary.json")
						]).then(function(data) {
							var target = document.querySelector('[data-component="cv1"]');
							var url = NYTG.VIRUS_ASSETS + '/build/js/dashboard.js';
							var props = { timeseries: data[0], timeseriesWorld: data[1], timeseriesCanada: data[2], counties: data[3], vaccine_summary: data[4], average_change_cases_two_weeks: "-16", average_change_deaths_two_weeks: "-30", average_change_cases_two_weeks_world: "11", average_change_deaths_two_weeks_world: "-11", average_change_cases_two_weeks_can: "1", average_change_deaths_two_weeks_can: "-38", us_maps: ["usa_map","vaccine_distribution"], int_maps: ["world_map","vaccine_map","usa_map"], show_county: true, type: "top-stories" }

							
							let component;

							NYTG.load(url).then((mod) => {
								const Component = mod.default;

								component = new Component({
									target,
									hydrate: true,
									props
								});
							});
						
						});
                      </script>
                      <!-- ASSET : END -->
                     </div>
                     <!-- story footer -->
                    </div>
                    <!-- /end story-body -->

                    <script>
                     ;(function() {
  // NYT apps resize function
  // Resizes the interactive webview height after a 1 second pause
  // Don't run resizer if it's in a programming list webview
  if ( window.NYTG && window.NYTG.enqueue && !document.querySelector("#programming-list") ) {
    setTimeout(function() {
      var container = document.querySelector("#g-2020-03-16-coronavirus-maps-embed");
      var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
      function resize() {
        var height = container.offsetHeight;
        window.NYTG.enqueue(
          JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } })
        )
      }
      window.addEventListener("resize", function() {
        if ( window.innerWidth != windowWidth ) {
          windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
          resize();
        }
      });
      resize();
    }, 1000);
  }

})();
                    </script>

                      <script type="text/javascript">
                       ;(function() {

    clearInterval(window.hpFaderTimer_international);

    var images = document.querySelectorAll('#international-home-fader.g-home-fader .g-home-fader-photo-wrap'),
      counter = 0;

    var hasCaptions = true;
    var speed = hasCaptions ? 7500 : 5000

    window.hpFaderTimer_international = setInterval(function() {
      var prev = counter;
      counter++;
      if(counter >  images.length-1) counter = 0
        images[counter].classList.add('g-home-fader-photo-active');
        // console.log(prev, counter)

        setTimeout(function(){
          // console.log(prev, counter)
         images[prev].classList.remove('g-home-fader-photo-active');
        }, 250)
    },  speed);

    // NYT app detection code
    var isInApp = !!(
      // sometimes this query param is present
      window.location.search.indexOf('nytapp') > -1 ||
      // usually the user agent is set
      window.navigator.userAgent.match(/nyt[-_]?(?:ios|android)/i) ||
      // on hybrid articles in android, the user agent and qs is missing
      (window.navigator.userAgent.match(/android/i) && window.__HYBRID__)
    );

    var isInAppHome = document.querySelector('.nytapp-home-interactive') !== null;
    var isAndroid = window.navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Android') > -1;
    var isIos = !!window.navigator.userAgent.match(/iP(hone|ad)/i);

    if (isInApp && isAndroid) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-android');
    if (isInApp && isIos) document.querySelector('html').classList.add('nytapp-ios');

    // don't resize if inside of programming list
    if (!document.querySelector("#programming-list")) {
    // NYT apps resize function
    // Resizes the interactive webview height after a 1 second pause
      if ( window.NYTG && window.NYTG.enqueue) {
        setTimeout(function() {
          var container = document.querySelector("#international-home-fader.g-home-fader");
          var windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
          function resize() {
            var height = container.offsetHeight;
            window.NYTG.enqueue(
              JSON.stringify({ id: 0, type: 'resize', options: { height: height } })
              )
          }
          window.addEventListener("resize", function() {
            if ( window.innerWidth != windowWidth ) {
              windowWidth = window.innerWidth;
              resize();
            }
          });
          resize();
        }, 1000);
      }
    }

  })();
                      </script>
